---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import { topics, allPosts } from '../lib/content';
const posts = await allPosts();
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About this research library.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">About</h1>
    <div class="prose-research mt-8">
      <p>
        This is a growing library of <strong>{posts.length} deep-dive notes</strong> across
        <strong>{topics.length} topics</strong> — from staff-level system design and distributed
        systems to economics, clear thinking, and money. Each topic is written to take you from
        plain-language intuition, to precise mechanics, to the failure modes that show up in the
        real world.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unlike most online write-ups, these aren't cheat sheets. They include back-of-the-envelope
        math, worked examples, comparison tables, war stories, and test-yourself questions. They're
        meant to be read slowly and worked through.
      </p>
      <h2>Why this exists</h2>
      <p>
        I research these topics in depth for my own learning and work, and publish the evergreen
        parts here so they can help others learning the same things. New topics get added over time.
      </p>
      <h2>Stay in the loop</h2>
      <p>Subscribe below to get an email when a substantial new topic or post lands.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
